Day-2:----[Networking]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. IP Addressing
What is an IP Address?
An IP address is a unique address assigned to every system in a network.
Example:`192.168.1.10`
Two types:Public IP  → Used on the internet
          Private IP → Used inside local networks
Check IP Address in Linux :ip addr  (or) ifconfig
Interview Point :Explain that IP addresses help systems communicate over networks.

2. Subnetting Basics
Subnetting divides a network into smaller networks.
Example: IP: `192.168.1.10/24`
Here:`/24` means subnet mask `255.255.255.0`
This allows: 254 usable hosts
Why Used?
* Better security
* Better network management
* Reduced traffic

3. TCP/IP Model[Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol]
TCP/IP is the communication protocol used in networking.
Main Layers:
1. Application Layer
2. Transport Layer
3. Internet Layer
4. Network Access Layer

Important Protocols
* HTTP/HTTPS → Websites
* SSH → Secure remote login
* FTP → File transfer
* DNS → Name resolution

4. DNS (Domain Name System)
DNS converts domain names into IP addresses.
Example:`google.com` → `142.x.x.x`
DNS Commands : nslookup google.com (or) dig google.com
Interview Answer :“DNS is used to resolve domain names into IP addresses.”

5. SSH Configuration
SSH allows secure remote access to Linux servers.
Install SSH       : sudo yum install openssh-server (or) sudo apt install openssh-server
Start SSH         : sudo systemctl start sshd
Enable SSH        : sudo systemctl enable sshd
Connect to Server : ssh username@ipaddress

6. FTP Configuration
FTP transfers files between systems.
Install FTP Server : sudo yum install vsftpd
Start FTP          : sudo systemctl start vsftpd
Enable FTP         : sudo systemctl enable vsftpd
Check FTP Port     : netstat -tulnp
Default FTP Port   :`21`

7. Apache Web Server Setup
Install Apache  : For RHEL/CentOS: sudo yum install httpd
                  For Ubuntu     : sudo apt install apache2
Start Service   : sudo systemctl start httpd
Enable Service  : sudo systemctl enable httpd
Check Status    : systemctl status httpd
Access Website  : http://server-ip

8. Nginx Setup
Install Nginx : sudo yum install nginx
Start Nginx   : sudo systemctl start nginx
Enable Nginx  : sudo systemctl enable nginx

9. Firewall Configuration
Linux firewalls protect servers.
Common tools:
* iptables
* firewalld
Check Firewall : sudo firewall-cmd --state
Open HTTP Port : sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=http
Reload Firewall: sudo firewall-cmd --reload

10. Port Checking
Check Open Ports : netstat -tulnp (or) ss -tulnp
Important Ports:
* 22 → SSH
* 80 → HTTP
* 443 → HTTPS
* 21 → FTP

